29/07/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Sea, Tourism, Transport and Development Minister Bozidar Kalmeta has decided to dismiss all members of the management board of the state-run railway, local media reported on Tuesday (July 28th). The decision was taken in co-ordination with Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor. Kalmeta has vowed to punish those responsible for last week's train derailment near Split that left six people dead and at least 50 injured. (HRT, HINA, Jutarnji List, Poslovni Dnevnik - 28/07/09)
